      "text": "I (Pamela) have a problem picturing that.  Back when I was a child people sat round the radio and listened to it (like they might sit down to watch TV now), but I think of radio now as something people turn on when they are doing other things and probably on their own, unless it is music, or something else \"in the background\".  It would help to know how the current audience of SOAS listen to the programmes. "
